question_title: Will the interest in “amy klobuchar” change between 2026-02-05 and 2026-02-12 according to Google Trends?
summary: Amy Klobuchar's Google Trends interest spiked to 93 on Jan 29 when she announced her Minnesota governor run, but has since decayed to ~9 (Feb 4). Values appear stabilized at this elevated baseline. No major campaign events are scheduled for Feb 5-12 (caucuses were Feb 3, conventions are in March). The ±3 threshold is tight relative to typical day-to-day volatility at low values. "Doesn't change" is favored as the status quo, but her active governor campaign and the ongoing Minnesota immigration story create meaningful upside potential. Limited downside given values are already near baseline (floor around 5-6).

factors.description: Post-announcement spike has decayed and stabilized around 9-11, suggesting baseline equilibrium during forecast period
No major campaign events scheduled Feb 5-12 (caucuses already occurred Feb 3, conventions in March)
Active governor campaign increases chance of news-driven interest spike (polling, endorsements, controversy)
Minnesota immigration enforcement is ongoing national story that could boost Klobuchar attention
Floor effect: current value (~9) is close to baseline, limiting potential for >3 point decrease
±3 threshold is tight relative to observed daily volatility (3-14 range in quiet periods)
